## Supporting Types



<h4 id="devicepoolrule">Device<wbr>Pool<wbr>Rule</h4>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="attribute_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#attribute_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Attribute</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The rule's stringified attribute. Valid values are: <code>APPIUM_VERSION</code>, <code>ARN</code>, <code>AVAILABILITY</code>, <code>FLEET_TYPE</code>, <code>FORM_FACTOR</code>, <code>INSTANCE_ARN</code>, <code>INSTANCE_LABELS</code>, <code>MANUFACTURER</code>, <code>MODEL</code>, <code>OS_VERSION</code>, <code>PLATFORM</code>, <code>REMOTE_ACCESS_ENABLED</code>, <code>REMOTE_DEBUG_ENABLED</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="operator_csharp">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies how Device Farm compares the rule's attribute to the value. For the operators that are supported by each attribute. Valid values are: <code>EQUALS</code>, <code>NOT_IN</code>, <code>IN</code>, <code>GREATER_THAN</code>, <code>GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUALS</code>, <code>LESS_THAN</code>, <code>LESS_THAN_OR_EQUALS</code>, <code>CONTAINS</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">

## Import


DeviceFarm Device Pools can be imported by their arn

```sh
 $ pulumi import aws:devicefarm/devicePool:DevicePool example arn:aws:devicefarm:us-west-2:123456789012:devicepool:4fa784c7-ccb4-4dbf-ba4f-02198320daa1/4fa784c7-ccb4-4dbf-ba4f-02198320daa1
```
